The course gives an overview of the development and background of the hellenistic poetry and of the changes compared to the classical period. The texts of the most recognized authors are read, their style compared to each other and to the style of the authors already familiar from the classical period.Objectives/eesmärkid:  During the course the hellenistic lyric and shorter poetical forms are discussed through most important keywords and themes, concentrating on the poetic texts of the most prominent representatives of this period.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After attending the course the students have aquainted themselves with the basic forms and most recognized authors of the hellenistic poetry. They understand the main themes of the non-classical period, where the authors took an interest in style, form and describing the feelings of an individual.
